[EXPERIMENT LOG]
Date: 2026-04-08
Feature set: MFCC + Voiced-Ratio (F0 removed)

DECISION
Removed F0 features (mean_f0, std_f0) from the feature vector.
Retained: 13 MFCC means, 13 MFCC stds, voiced_ratio (27 features total).

REASON
PCA on the full MFCC + F0 feature set was producing a clear diagonal
gender boundary in PC1 vs PC2, separating female speakers (1, 6) from
male speakers (2-5) regardless of keyword. The dominant source of variance
was absolute F0 level (female ~2x male pitch), which PCA greedily captured
as its primary axis. This suppressed word-level signal.

OUTCOME
Removing F0 eliminated the gender diagonal. PC1 now appears more
word-driven. Centroid separation between dance and sing improved along PC1.
Overall within-word speaker scatter is reduced but still significant.
Speaker 6 centroids remain outliers, suggesting residual speaker-identity
variance is still present.

CONCLUSION
F0 removal was necessary but is likely too aggressive as a permanent fix.
Absolute F0 level is the problem, not F0 itself. Pitch contour shape and
rhythm are word-discriminative features being lost by full removal.

NEXT STEPS
1. Implement per-speaker F0 normalization (subtract speaker mean, divide
   by speaker std) to preserve relative pitch contour while removing
   the male/female offset.
2. Reintroduce normalized F0 features and compare against current results.
3. Proceed to multi-label LDA on whichever feature set performs better.